cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The regular number of a graph is a combinatorial parameter that relates to the partition of the edge set of a graph. This suggests a connection to discrete mathematics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The regular number of a graph can be seen as a measure of the complexity of the graph, which is a topic of interest in data structures and algorithms.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): Graph partitioning is a common problem in computational geometry, and the regular number of a graph can be seen as a special case of graph partitioning.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): Graph partitioning is also a topic of interest in game theory, and the regular number of a graph can be seen as a measure of the fairness of a partition.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Graph partitioning is a common problem in social and information networks, and the regular number of a graph can be seen as a measure of the regularity of the network structure.
